5|$|In its raw form, {{tungsten}} {{is a hard}} <b>steel-grey</b> <b>metal</b> that {{is often}} brittle and hard to work. If made very pure, tungsten retains its hardness (which exceeds that of many steels), and becomes malleable enough {{that it can be}} worked easily. It is worked by forging, drawing, or extruding. Tungsten objects are also commonly formed by sintering.|$|E

